<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146129>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Diagnostic features of Limomium lanfrancoi. A. Habit. B. Stem article. C. Inflorescence. D. Spikelets. E. Inner bracts in lateral view. F. Inner bracts in dorsal view. G. Middle bracts. H. Outer bracts. I. Calyces. J. Calyx lobes. Illustration by S. Brullo based on living material coming from the type locality (CAT)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146129/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146137>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Geographical distribution of Limomium lanfrancoi (red dot) in Cominotto. From Google Earth (modified)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146137/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146139>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Phenological features of Limonium lanfrancoi from Cominotto. A–C. Individuals in natural habitat. D–E. Rocky coast with L. lanfrancoi. F. Blue Lagoon between Comino and Cominotto. (Photos A–D by M. E. Galea, E–F by S. Cambria)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146139/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146141>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Distribution of Limonium species in the MalteseArchipelago.Green dots:Limonium melitense; blue dots:Limonium virgatum; purple dots: Limonium zeraphae; red dot: Limonium lanfrancoi. It is based only on examined specimens listed in the paper." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146141/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

